The Federal Executive Council (FEC) has Wednesday approved the renaming of the Federal Ministry of Communications to be called Federal Ministry of Communications and Digital Economy.  The honorable Minister heading the Ministry; Dr Isa Pantami who disclosed this while briefing State House Correspondents at the Villa at the end of FEC meeting chaired by Vice President prof. Yemi Osinbajo; said the change is in compliance with global standard and to reflect the evolvement of Digital technology around the world.  He said the new Ministry is already developing the digital economic policies, infrastructure and capacity building to ensure Nigerians are digitally literate. He also said the Nigerian Communication Commission (NCC) has been directed to ensure the cancellation of the proposed USSD charges by MTN.  Also speaking, the Minister of Labour and Employment, Sen. Chris Ngige said FEC approved the take-off date for the implementation of the consequential adjustments of the new National minimum wage with effect from 18th April 2019 and payment be made on or before December 31st 2019. He said States have been directed to meet with Labour union in respective states to ensure proper negotiations and implementation of the new Minimum wage adding that template for the new wage would be forwarded to the various state Governments.  Our State House Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the Minister of Aviation, Sen. Hadi Sirika said the Council Approved the procurement and installation of Communication equipments and ATC Consol at the airports in Katsina and Zaria, Kaduna state in order to improve communication and safety in aviation sector.